Network Topology

- Physical  
  - How plugged in  
- Logical  
  - How data flows  
- Common types  
  - P2P (Point to Point)  
    - Direct link betw/ nodes  
  - Bus  
    - All devices share a single backbone cable  
    - Cost effective if small network  
    - Prone to collision  
  - Ring  
    - Each device connects to 2 neighbors forming a loop  
    - Uses token passing  
    - Minimal collision  
    - Single failure can disrupt network  
  - Star  
    - All devices connect to a central hub  
  - Mesh  
    - Every devices connect to every other (full) or some (partial) devices  
    - Highly reliable/secure  
    - Costly  
  - Tree  
    - Hierarchical structure  
    - Combine star and bus  
    - Scalable  
    - Central hub failure impacts the network  
  - Hybrid  
    - Combination of topologies  
    - Offer flexibility  
    - High design/maintenance cost

